<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-239-706  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 239 706.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  March 1990 v7 n2 p65(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Implementing management metrics: an Army program. (US ArmyCommunications-Electronics Command's Cecom program; includesrelated articles on implementing management metrics, the Cecomprogram's roots, and the essence of management metrics)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fenick, Stewart.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Advanced Software Technology operation of the US ArmyCommunications-Electronics Command's (Cecom's) Center for SoftwareEngineering is developing a software management metrics system forthe monitoring and management of the entire development life cycleof 'large, complex, mission-critical' software systems.andP;  Mostcurrent monitoring and control strategies for such softwareprojects are inefficient and cumbersome, often resulting ininadequate software delivered late and at excessive cost.andP;  The newCecom management metrics, the Army Materiel Command SoftwareIndicators for Management Insight and Management Quality Insight,consists of six management and seven quality indicators tooptimize acquisition strategy, organizational efficiency, productquality and delivery, programming productivity, system support andcustomer satisfaction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Militarym Research and DevelopmentSoftware MetricsManagement of EDPPerformance ImprovementApplications ProgrammingImplementationUnited States. Army. Communications-Electronics Command.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Waterfall development and corresponding metrics-application lifecycles. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>